üì¢CASTING CALL

‚ÄúJust Blokes‚Äù, a new piece of Scottish writing by Tori Kay

Water Horse Productions is seeking performers for Just Blokes, a dark comedy exploring men‚Äôs mental health through friendship, masculinity, and the ignorance of youth.

Written by Tori Kay, Artistic Director of Water Horse Productions, and produced by Tori Kay and Zoe Keddie (Co‚ÄìArtistic Director), the production is intended for Edinburgh Festival Fringe 2026.

About the Play‚Ä¶

Just Blokes examines how young men navigate friendship, vulnerability, and emotional responsibility in a culture that often encourages silence. Through humour, sharp dialogue, and moments of discomfort, the play asks how we can better advocate for ourselves and each other.

Genre: Dark Comedy
Themes: Friendship, masculinity, mental health, youth, emotional ignorance

Roles Available‚Ä¶

Four Men (20s) ‚Äì Main Cast
Each character is distinct, flawed, and fully realised, with individual quirks and shortcomings as outlined in the character briefs. Performers should be comfortable with emotionally honest material, fast-paced dialogue, and comedic timing.

Two Women (20s) ‚Äì Supporting Roles
Playing ‚Äúthe girls‚Äù ‚Äî smaller but significant roles that contrast and reflect the blokes‚Äô relationships with women, intimacy, and femininity.

Who We‚Äôre Looking For‚Ä¶

Strong actors with an interest in new writing

Ability to handle dark comedy and sensitive themes with care

Collaborative, open, and thoughtful creatives

Scottish accents welcome but not essential

SUBMISSION DETAILS

Deadline: 31st January 2026

Further details will be provided upon expression of interest

MIT EINEM FILMFEUERWERK INS NEUE JAHR

Bevor das alte Jahr sich verabschiedet,  pr√§sentieren wir bereits die ersten Highlights 2026.
Nach einer Vorlage von Albert Camus kommt mit DER FREMDE franz√∂sisches Kino auf die Leinwand.

Ob sich ein weiterer Film aus Europa, die spanische Produktion SORDA - DER KLANG WELT f√ºr einen Besuch im Kronenkino Mistelbach lohnt, erfahren Sie bei uns.

Und wir starten im neuen Jahr mit der Kooperation mit Cinema Next, die √∂sterreichischen Talenten eine Plattform gibt mit Simon Maria Kubiena.

Weitere Filmtipps sowie Themes und Songs aus den besten Filmen aller Zeiten werden wie immer von Filmexpertin Sarah Fuchs ins richtige Licht ger√ºckt.

items.text:
Fabulous review of the KITTEL script from Dr Philippa Byrne of University of Oxford's Centre of Intellectual Studies.  

"It's not my period of history, but I found it fascinating as an exploration of complicity, and ambition versus personal integrity. Kittel's life is a strikingly productive way to examine those themes, especially because - to a modern audience - he is a relative unknown, and it is hard (at first glance) to imagine how an academic working in such an esoteric field would become so valuable to the Nazi movement. I found the framing with Leonore and Stolz really compelling too, as an examination of how difficult academic institutions find it to reckon with its own past or to be challenged on their records."

KITTEL premieres January 2026 Liverpool Unity Theatre

MPhttps://intellectualhistory.web.ox.ac.uk/people/undefined-0

We are now casting our  Spring show  Shake Rattle And Roll and looking for self Contained experienced hardworking performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community .The 
The show is a celebration  to  all the  greatest songs and  stars of the 50s 60s  70s The Beatles ,Elvis,  Doris Day, Connie Francis ,Cliff Richard, Buddy Holly  and more.
Dates
Rehearsals- 23rd -27th February 
Playing Dates- 
We work Monday to Friday  (2 x 60 minute shows per day) 
Casting Breakdown We are now looking for  strong /experienced Male and Female singer /performers 
The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced performers that can hold an audience and are looking for engaging vocalist performers.
We are looking for drivers with cars only .
We  are looking for performers  on all area of the UK -please include bases when sending details.
We are offering 700 per week plus fuel  on the road  
Please send details including a singing reel to info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

*CALL FOR CROWD PARTICIPANTS (EXTRAS) // UNPAID*

*Berlin, SO36, 04.01.2026*

For our student short film project _Signal One_ we are looking for people to be part of the *background crowd* in a punk club scene, shot at *SO36 Berlin* around noon on *January 4th, 2026* .

What the movie is about: _After meeting face-to-face with the punk scene in 1977s West Berlin, a Yugoslav philosophy student has to learn how to confront and accept the person he really is._

We are looking for around 50 people who want to go wild in a *70s punk club scene* and are happy to dress accordingly. All ages and all genders welcome!

Unfortunately, the project is unpaid but we will provide snacks on set. Estimated shooting time: *approx. 3-4 hours* , starting around noon.

If you‚Äôre interested or want more information, feel free to text me by phone or send an email to signalone.casting@posteo.de. 

Looking forward to hearing from you :)

--- 

*German Version:*

F√ºr unser studentisches Kurzfilmprojekt Signal One suchen wir Leute, die *Teil der Crowd* (Kompars*innen) in einer *Punkclub-Szene* sein m√∂chten. Die Szene wird am 04.01.2026 gegen Mittag im *SO36 Berlin* gedreht.

Worum es im Film geht:

_Nachdem er der Punk-Szene im West-Berlin von 1977 begegnet ist, muss ein jugoslawischer Philosophiestudent lernen, sich seiner eigenen Identit√§t zu stellen und diese zu akzeptieren._

Wir suchen ca. 50 Personen, die Lust haben, in einer *70er-Punkclub-Szene* die Partyg√§ste zu spielen und sich passend zu kleiden. Alle Altersgruppen und Geschlechter willkommen!

Das Projekt ist unbezahlt, aber es wird Snacks am Set geben.

Gesch√§tzte Drehzeit: *ca. 3‚Äì4 Stunden* , ab Mittag.

Wenn du interessiert bist oder mehr Informationen haben m√∂chtest, melde dich gern direkt unter dieser Nummer oder E-Mail an signalone.casting@posteo.de

Wir freuen uns auf eure Nachrichten! :)

items.text:
Hallo und gesundes neues Jahr euch! üôÇ

F√ºr ein kleines Filmprojekt, welches ich mit ein paar Freunden auf die Beine stellen wollte, suche ich seit einiger Zeit eine Laien-Darstellerin (ich hatte hier schonmal inseriert, vor einiger Zeit).  Rolle: Eine eiskalte Auftragskillerin.

Da wir das Drehbuch zusammen erstellen wollten, w√§r es sch√∂n , wenn du auch wirklich "intrinsischen" Spa√ü daran h√§ttest, in so eine Rolle zu schl√ºpfen.

Also, um es direkt zu sagen: Ein bisschen kranke Psychogedanken sollten mit im Spiel sein üòâ und ein bisschen Faible f√ºr Waffen w√§r auch nicht schlecht, aber  unter den klassischen Schauspielstudentinnen ist sowas leider nicht so oft zu finden.

Handlung des Films: Eine Auftragskillerin erwischt einen Privatdetektiv in ihrem Haus beim Durchsuchen ihrer Sachen. Sie stellt ihn zur Rede, fragt ihn ausf√ºhrlich aus und -entgegen dem sonst √ºblichen Krimi-Klischee der "Rettung in letzter Sekunde" - exekutiert ihn. D√ºster. Realistisch. Eiskalt.

Drehort soll entweder Berlin oder Bayreuth sein, mit meiner kleinen Pen&Paper-Rollenspielgruppe im April. Aber auch, wenn du von weiter weg kommst: Hilfe am Drehbuch oder eigene Ideen einbringen geht immer.

items.text:
Open theatre auditions coming up at The South Devon Players Theatre & Film Company, Brixham

DEVON/ OPEN BOOK PROFITSHARE / THEATRE / ANY GENDER OR ETHNICITY/

- Roles open for actors aged 16 to the sky's the limit. 

- A lot of the roles in our staging of this play  are not bound by gender; we are looking for the strongest actor for each roles. 

- Any ethnicity/ accent/ experience level equally welcome. What we are looking for are great performance skills, pleasant friendly teamwork, and the desire to be an active part of a really excellent quality show. 

- The show is set in 1793. The show is suitable for all audiences. 

- Period costumes made and supplied for all cast. 

- if you cannot make auditions on January 25th please contact us to arrange an audition over the two weeks before. 

- Actors should be based in, or have a base in, Devon because of attending rehearsals and performances. Sorry none of us who are regulars with the theatre team are in a financial or housing position to be able to put people up from further afield. We have a performance in London but have a minibus fundraised for, to get people there and back to Devon. 

- Our show teams are diverse in terms of age, experience, ethnicity and we usually have several neurodivergent team members - everyone coming on board should be willing to work as a part of a diverse group of people. 

- the show is profitshare for funding reasons. We cover rehearsal space/ costumes/ insurance etc by selling second hand bits on eBay and handmade jewellery in a couple of local shops.  This is on an open book process where ticket sales reports and any venue hire costs are shown upfront for perusal, and the ticket profits (Ticket sales less performance venue hire) are shared equally between each person in the show team. Sadly we cannot guarantee how much this is as it can vary wildly as is dependant on ticket sales. We constantly do our best to both promote the show to get those sales as high as possible and to apply for funding to bring everyone up to equity rates but this cant be guaranteed and we don‚Äôt believe in promising what we can‚Äôt guarantee to deliver. 

- ALL cast and crew also are given  access to portfolio photos and show video, copies of any press or promotional content featuring themselves, references on request (after completion of their first show run with us), and anything else that we find we can offer. 

- and - in answer to a common question we get:  nobody is ever charged anything to audition or perform with us.

Do please drop us a line with any questions not answered here or in the downloadable audition resources.

items.text:
**Are you craving real community in an often solitary industry?**

Sitting on a script, an idea, or a half-formed dream that keeps whispering **‚Äúyou should really do something with me‚Äù**?

Seeking a creative home where people actually show up, do the work, and support each other?

Ready to deepen your craft, develop projects, and take charge of your career in 2026?

**Come join us at Modern Rituals.**

Step into a year of bold storytelling, rigorous craft, and genuine artistic community.

Modern Rituals is:
* **A production company** for film, TV, and theatre
* **A members hub** for working professional actors, writers, directors, and producers with a full programme of monthly labs designed to sharpen your skills, expand your toolkit and move your projects forward.
* **A creative community** connecting artists through in-person socials in Soho, London, with industry guests like the Oscar Nominated + Golden Globe winning producer Celine Rattray (April 2025).

We bring together artists who want to go deeper ‚Äî in their work and careers, in their collaborations, and as humans. 

**Monthly Labs (2026)**

A rotating programme of labs designed to sharpen your skills, stretch your range, and gently nudge your projects into the world:

* **Writers WorkshopÔøΩ**
Writing for stage and screen ‚Äî from first idea to polished script.
* **Accent Gym**ÔøΩ
Build a versatile arsenal of accents for auditions and roles.
* **Stage Animal **
In-person theatre lab to develop stage craft, presence, and confidence.
* **Meisner MethodÔøΩ**
In-person Meisner training focused on truthful, moment-to-moment acting. Brave work. No hiding.
* **Shakespeare SessionsÔøΩ**
In-depth classical text lab leading to a Shakespeare theatre project in September 2026.
* **Power ProducerÔøΩ **
Level up pitches, finance plans, budgeting, investor strategy, and troubleshoot live projects.
* **On Screen MagicÔøΩ**
Shoot 2‚Äì3 page new-writing scenes on professional kit for showreels, proof of concepts, and development.
* **Self Tape PracticeÔøΩ **
Real-world audition simulation: script out Monday, review together Friday to watch, learn and refine choices and technical setup.

**Community**
* **Weekly Support + Accountability Group** ÔøΩ
Set bold goals with fellow artists. Stay accountable. Challenge and lift each other up on career and life journeys.
* **Private WhatsApp GroupÔøΩ** 
Ongoing connection, collaboration, and support.
* **Regular Soho SocialsÔøΩ **
Network and connect with industry guests ‚Äî like Oscar-nominated & Golden Globe-winning producer Celine Rattray (April 2025).

**Productions**

**And yes ‚Äî we actually make things too.**

Members can plug into our active development slate:
* 2 films
* 3 TV series
* 3 plays

**Spotlight**: Shakespeare theatre project (September 2026), born from our Shakespeare Sessions lab.

Explore the full slate at modernrituals.art/slate

**Join Us in 2026**
* First lab is free
* Then ¬£40/month to join the community (cancel anytime)

If you‚Äôre looking for a like-minded hub of artists sharpening their craft, developing bold work, and taking real steps forward ‚Äî Modern Rituals is for you.

**Join now.ÔøΩ**
Sharpen your craft.ÔøΩ
Grow as a human.ÔøΩ
Bring your next project closer to the screen or stage in 2026.

Check us out at www.modernrituals.art or on insta @m0dernrituals

items.text:
Spend two extraordinary weeks living and breathing Shakespeare.

Monsieur Shakespeare is an open, welcoming summer theatre residency for amateur and community performers who want to go deeper, without needing to be ‚Äúprofessional‚Äù.

Set in the sun-soaked countryside of south-west France, the course combines:

‚Ä¢ ensemble-led actor training
‚Ä¢ playful, practical work on Shakespeare‚Äôs language
‚Ä¢ rehearsal towards a fully staged outdoor performance
‚Ä¢ and the simple joy of living, eating and creating together

Led by Peter Bramley and the expert team at Pants on Fire Theatre Company, the work draws on Lecoq-inspired physical theatre, Meisner, text clarity, generosity of ensemble and bold storytelling. The emphasis is always on confidence, craft and collaboration, not pressure or pretence.

‚ÄúI came thinking it would be a holiday with a bit of acting. I left feeling braver, clearer, and genuinely changed as a performer, and as a person.‚Äù Monsieur Shakespeare 2025 Participant.

Participants come from the UK, US and across Europe. Some have decades of experience, others are returning to theatre after a long break. What they share is curiosity, commitment, and a love of Shakespeare brought vividly into the present.

You will rehearse and perform in beautiful historic outdoor spaces at Mas d‚ÄôArjac, share long communal meals, swim, laugh, and leave with sharper skills, new friendships, and a genuine sense of achievement.

üé≠ Training. Ensemble. Performance. Summer.
If this speaks to you, or to someone in your group, please share, and come and join us.

https://www.pantsonfiretheatre.com/monsieur-shakespeare

üéâüé≠EXCITING AUDITION OPPORTUNITY!!üé≠üéâ

Following a successful run of our previous production ‚ÄúI Did Something I Have‚Äù at Edinburgh Fringe Festival in 2024‚Ä¶we are now staging our biggest production yet!

‚ÄúNOT SO STAR-CROSSED‚Äù is a brand new play by playwright Paul-James Green that will make its World Premiere at the Epstein Theatre in Liverpool.

The Little Bridges Theatre Company are due to perform Romeo and Juliet in their final attempt to save their theatre from financial ruin, as if the financial situation was not bad enough, their overbearing, longstanding director is destroying the play and clashing constantly with his leading man...what makes it worse is the director drops dead midway through the process...the chairman has no idea how the theatre will survive, especially when both his leading man and leading lady look as if they will walk...fate intervenes when a black listed West End Director enters the theatre to seek help after his car breaks down...and things become even worse...

Performance dates are 26th and 27th June (1 evening show on the 26th then a matinee and evening on th 27th)

Although this is an unpaid opportunity, the chance to appear in the World Premiere of a brand new play, in such an iconic venue would be just as amazing to be involved in!

If you are interested in auditioning please e-mail pjgproductionsofficial@gmail.com titling the email ‚ÄúCasting NSSC‚Äù and the roles you wish to go for! :)

**Casting Call for a 20-min short**

Hi everyone! We‚Äôre looking for non-union actors who are based on Vancouver, BC. We're thrilled to have new blood in our team!

**Production Information:**

-Location: Vancouver, BC

-Shoot Dates: Feb 21st-22nd.

-Genre:Drama, Thriller

-Non-Union/Volunteer

-Crafty+IMDb credit provided

**Roles:**

**Officer Shaw Male 28-50**

A true believer in justice and law enforcement. He doesn‚Äôt believe mentalism is anything more than cheap party tricks, but he finds Chaz and his shtick entertaining, so he allows Chaz to perform for him and explain himself. With every word Chaz says in his defence, Officer Shaw starts to see through Chaz‚Äôs persona and eventually confronts him about the moral, ethical and legal complications his profession entails. The conversation reaches a boiling point when Chaz attempts to read Officer Shaw‚Äôs mind by repeating the last words spoken to Shaw from his missing daughter.

**To submit:**

Please submit headshot and demo reel to **theartofreadingminds.short@gmail.com** and indicate which role you‚Äôd like to be considered for.

**AUDITION NOTICE** -- LOVE, LOSS AND WHAT I WORE

Authors: Nora Ephron and Delia Ephron (based on the book by Ilene Beckerman)
Director: Olivia Etey
Producer: Janet Ellis
Audition Date/Time: Tuesday, January 6, 7 PM
Location: Peninsula Productions (14600 North Bluff Road, White Rock)

Preparation: Please prepare two short 1-2 minute monologues. One comedic and one dramatic.
Play Summary:

Love, Loss, and What I Wore uses a series of monologues and ensemble vignettes to explore the
female experience through the lens of fashion. By using clothing as a "time capsule," the play
recounts pivotal life moments‚Äîmarriages, heartbreaks, and family dynamics‚Äîall triggered by
memories of specific garments. From the universal struggle of bra shopping to poignant stories of
resilience and grief, the production highlights how a woman‚Äôs wardrobe serves as a roadmap of her
identity and history.

Characters:
The play features a diverse ensemble of 5‚Äì7 women ages 40+. Except for Gingy, all actors portray
multiple characters.

Gingy: The central narrator and anchor of the play. She is wise and self-deprecating,
recounting her life story from childhood through several marriages and milestones.
Ensemble A (The Matriarch/Dramatist): Primarily portrays mother figures and women
navigating deep loss or family traditions.
Ensemble B (The Comedian): Handles high-energy, humorous rants regarding fashion
frustrations, such as the "I Hate My Purse" monologue.
Ensemble C (The Survivor): Focuses on characters navigating life‚Äôs hardships, including stories
of illness, aging, and reclaiming personal power.
Ensemble D (The Ingenue/Rebel): Portrays younger characters dealing with first loves,
wedding dress shopping, and finding their identity through style.

This staged reading will be at Peninsula Studio Theatre from March 5, 6, 7, 8, 2026. Rehearsals will
be in January - March 2026. Actors are paid an honourarium and get free parking.

If you would like to audition, please send your headshot and resume to
janet@peninsulaproductions.org 

We look forward to hearing from you!

 #peninsulaproductions #arts #culture #theatre #stage #supporthearts #surreybc #auditions #actors

items.text:
Open theatre auditions coming up at The South Devon Players Theatre & Film Company, Brixham

DEVON/ OPEN BOOK PROFITSHARE / THEATRE / ANY GENDER OR ETHNICITY/

- Roles open for actors aged 16 to the sky's the limit. 

- A lot of the roles in our staging of this play  are not bound by gender; we are looking for the strongest actor for each roles. 

- Any ethnicity/ accent/ experience level equally welcome. What we are looking for are great performance skills, pleasant friendly teamwork, and the desire to be an active part of a really excellent quality show. 

- The show is set in 1793. The show is suitable for all audiences. 

- Period costumes made and supplied for all cast. 

- if you cannot make auditions on January 25th please contact us to arrange an audition over the two weeks before. 

- Actors should be based in, or have a base in, Devon because of attending rehearsals and performances. Sorry none of us who are regulars with the theatre team are in a financial or housing position to be able to put people up from further afield. We have a performance in London but have a minibus fundraised for, to get people there and back to Devon. 

- Our show teams are diverse in terms of age, experience, ethnicity and we usually have several neurodivergent team members - everyone coming on board should be willing to work as a part of a diverse group of people. 

- the show is profitshare for funding reasons. We cover rehearsal space/ costumes/ insurance etc by selling second hand bits on eBay and handmade jewellery in a couple of local shops.  This is on an open book process where ticket sales reports and any venue hire costs are shown upfront for perusal, and the ticket profits (Ticket sales less performance venue hire) are shared equally between each person in the show team. Sadly we cannot guarantee how much this is as it can vary wildly as is dependant on ticket sales. We constantly do our best to both promote the show to get those sales as high as possible and to apply for funding to bring everyone up to equity rates but this cant be guaranteed and we don‚Äôt believe in promising what we can‚Äôt guarantee to deliver. 

- ALL cast and crew also are given  access to portfolio photos and show video, copies of any press or promotional content featuring themselves, references on request (after completion of their first show run with us), and anything else that we find we can offer. 

- and - in answer to a common question we get:  nobody is ever charged anything to audition or perform with us.

Do please drop us a line with any questions not answered here or in the downloadable audition resources.

üì¢CASTING CALL

‚ÄúJust Blokes‚Äù, a new piece of Scottish writing by Tori Kay

Water Horse Productions is seeking performers for Just Blokes, a dark comedy exploring men‚Äôs mental health through friendship, masculinity, and the ignorance of youth.

Written by Tori Kay, Artistic Director of Water Horse Productions, and produced by Tori Kay and Zoe Keddie (Co‚ÄìArtistic Director), the production is intended for Edinburgh Festival Fringe 2026.

About the Play‚Ä¶

Just Blokes examines how young men navigate friendship, vulnerability, and emotional responsibility in a culture that often encourages silence. Through humour, sharp dialogue, and moments of discomfort, the play asks how we can better advocate for ourselves and each other.

Genre: Dark Comedy
Themes: Friendship, masculinity, mental health, youth, emotional ignorance

Roles Available‚Ä¶

Four Men (20s) ‚Äì Main Cast
Each character is distinct, flawed, and fully realised, with individual quirks and shortcomings as outlined in the character briefs. Performers should be comfortable with emotionally honest material, fast-paced dialogue, and comedic timing.

Two Women (20s) ‚Äì Supporting Roles
Playing ‚Äúthe girls‚Äù ‚Äî smaller but significant roles that contrast and reflect the blokes‚Äô relationships with women, intimacy, and femininity.

Who We‚Äôre Looking For‚Ä¶

Strong actors with an interest in new writing

Ability to handle dark comedy and sensitive themes with care

Collaborative, open, and thoughtful creatives

Scottish accents welcome but not essential

SUBMISSION DETAILS

Deadline: 31st January 2026

Further details will be provided upon expression of interest

SONGS FROM LIFE ‚Äì mit Stefanie Rummel
üìç Gallus Theater Frankfurt
üóì 10.01.2026 | ‚è∞ 20 Uhr

Vielen herzlichen Dank f√ºr den tollen Artikel in der Frankfurter Rundschau ‚Äì ein gro√ües Dankesch√∂n an die Redakteurin Sonja Laud f√ºr die sch√∂ne Berichterstattung! üôè‚ú® Frankfurter Rundschau 

SONGS FROM LIFE ‚Äì 10.01.2026
Gesang, der ber√ºhrt. Geschichten, die verwandeln.
Deutschlandpremiere

Adresse: Gallus Theater, Kleyerstr. 15, 60326 Frankfurt, T:758060-20
Ticketverkauf:  https://www.gallustheater.de/prog/vob.php?i=4

Die preisgekr√∂nte S√§ngerin Stefanie Rummel nimmt das Publikum mit auf eine fesselnde musikalische Reise ‚Äì von den Pariser Caf√©s √ºber die Berliner Kabarettb√ºhnen bis in die Clubs Manhattans.
Mit Songs im Stil von Piaf, Weill, Sondheim und eigenen Kompositionen erz√§hlt sie von besonderen Momenten des Lebens ‚Äì voller Sehnsucht, Humor, Warmherzigkeit und Tiefe.
Als ‚Äûherzber√ºhrend‚Äú und mit ‚Äûbrillanter B√ºhnenpr√§senz‚Äú gefeiert, begeistert sie ihr Publikum in den USA, Gro√übritannien und ganz Europa ‚Äì und geht n√§chstes Jahr erneut in Australien auf Tournee.

Bernhard Lehner begleitet versiert am Fl√ºgel.
Sieben Songs stammen von Stefanie Rummel (Text & Musik) Diese Songs wurden in Kooperation mit Tom Schl√ºter produziert. (Pianist & Musikproduzent)
Ein Abend voller Gef√ºhl, Humor und internationalem Flair

SONGS FROM LIFE
Singing that touches. Stories that transform.
Australian Premiere

Award-winning singer Stefanie Rummel takes the audience on a captivating musical journey ‚Äì from the caf√©s of Paris to the cabaret stages of Berlin and the clubs of Manhattan.

With songs in the style of Piaf, Weill, Sondheim, as well as her own compositions, she tells stories of life‚Äôs special moments ‚Äì full of longing, humor, warmth, and depth.
Celebrated as ‚Äúheart-touching‚Äù and praised for her ‚Äúbrilliant stage presence,‚Äù she enchants audiences in the USA, the UK, and across Europe ‚Äì and will return to Australia on tour next year.

An inspiring, moving musical cabaret about life ‚Äì shaped by songs, personality, and storytelling.
Seven songs are written by Stefanie Rummel (lyrics & music). These songs were produced in collaboration with Tom Schl√ºter (pianist & music producer).
An evening full of emotion, humor, and international flair.

## CASTING CALL ‚Äî JERRY

**Project:** Short Film
**Genre:** Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller
**Shoot Location:** Lower Mainland, BC
**Shoot Days:** **Every Sunday ‚Äî Jan 18 to Feb 8**
**Compensation:** Volunteer / Passion Project

ABOUT THE PROJECT

A grounded, character-driven psychological drama exploring power, perception, and the cost of certainty in modern professional life. When Amber gains access to an experimental technology, she relies on it too much. The technology destabilizes her judgment, blurring truth, error, and perception.

ROLE: JERRY

**Age Range:** 35‚Äì45
**Gender:** Male
**Ethnicity:** **Caucasian**

CHARACTER SNAPSHOT

Jerry is Amber‚Äôs husband.
Quiet, intelligent, emotionally understated.

On the surface, he appears dependable and unremarkable ‚Äî someone who avoids conflict rather than causes it.
He is not flashy, not dominant, not overtly deceptive.

What makes Jerry compelling is contrast:
the gap between how he is perceived and what may be true beneath that surface.

Jerry is not written as a villain.
He is human, flawed, and emotionally evasive ‚Äî someone who slips rather than confronts.

PERFORMANCE NOTES

This role requires **restraint and realism**.

We are seeking an actor who can:
* Play emotional distance without coldness
* Convey inner conflict through minimal dialogue
* Avoid stereotypes or melodrama

Subtle behavioral shifts matter more than dialogue.

KEY TRAITS

Introverted
Intelligent
Conflict-avoidant
Emotionally restrained
Internally conflicted

AUDITION REQUIREMENTS

Self-tape audition
One short dramatic scene (sides to be provided)

SUBMISSION DETAILS

Please submit:
* Headshot
* Resume (if available)
* Demo reel or previous work

Email submissions to: **soultales.ca@gmail.com**
**Subject:** JERRY ‚Äì Casting Submission

NOTE!!!

This is a serious passion project with a small, committed team.

**Availability for all shoot days (Every Sunday from Jan 18 to Feb 8) is mandatory. **We are looking for actors who are reliable, prepared, and respectful of time and effort. Please apply only if you can fully commit to rehearsals, shoot days, and clear communication throughout the process. If you are unsure about your availability or commitment, we kindly ask that you do not apply.

## CASTING CALL ‚Äî TODD

**Project:** Short Film
**Genre:** Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller
**Shoot Location:** Lower Mainland, BC
**Shoot Days:** **Every Sunday ‚Äî Jan 18 to Feb 8**
**Compensation:** Volunteer / Passion Project

ABOUT THE PROJECT

A grounded, character-driven psychological drama exploring power, perception, and the cost of certainty in modern professional life. When Amber gains access to an experimental technology, she relies on it too much. The technology destabilizes her judgment, blurring truth, error, and perception.

ROLE: TODD

**Age Range:** 30‚Äì45
**Gender:** Male
**Ethnicity:** **Open / Race-agnostic**

CHARACTER SNAPSHOT

Todd is a colleague within the same professional ecosystem as Amber.
Competent, likable, and seemingly transparent.

He is not overtly manipulative or antagonistic.
What makes Todd unsettling is his **ordinariness** ‚Äî he appears honest, reasonable, and emotionally accessible.

As the story unfolds, ambiguity around his intentions grows.
Whether Todd is hiding something, misunderstood, or simply human is never fully resolved.

PERFORMANCE NOTES

This role requires **naturalism and restraint**.

We are looking for an actor who can:
* Play sincerity without exaggeration
* Hold ambiguity without signaling guilt or innocence
* Allow the audience to project meaning onto small behavioral shifts

No melodrama.
No villain performance.
Subtlety is essential.

KEY TRAITS

Approachable
Articulate
Emotionally readable ‚Äî but not transparent
Grounded
Unassuming

AUDITION REQUIREMENTS

Self-tape audition
One short dramatic scene (sides to be provided)

SUBMISSION DETAILS

Please submit:
* Headshot
* Resume (if available)
* Demo reel or previous work

Email submissions to: **soultales.ca@gmail.com**
**Subject:** TODD ‚Äì Casting Submission

NOTE!!!

This is a serious passion project with a small, committed team.

**Availability for all shoot days (Every Sunday from Jan 18 to Feb 8) is mandatory.**

We are looking for actors who are reliable, prepared, and respectful of time and effort.
Please apply only if you can fully commit to rehearsals, shoot days, and clear communication throughout the process.

If you are unsure about your availability or commitment, we kindly ask that you do not apply.

Veteos, a veterinary video production company, is working on a How-To series for pet parents. We are urgently seeing to hire dogs and cats who receive the following medications to film receiving their meds with their pet parent. Filming will be within the next few weeks.

Thanks!!

Hi all, happy New Year! I hope this is okay to post here...I am a local actor and recent USC grad looking to update my reel footage, and I wanted to see if there are any other actors out there who would be interested in filming a scene together to use for your reel as well?

I've produced a handful of short films and web series in the past and will happily write a scene based on your character type and provide you with raw and edited footage. I'm hoping to film in the South Denver/Littleton/Centennial area in mid-January (but flexible!) Let me know if you're interested; the best way to get in touch is via email to aspenksomers@gmail.com. TIA!

topComments.text: Ramiyah would have some interest. I will send an email Aspen

* *Arystokrata* - DIALOG W JƒòZYKU ANGIELSKIM (British English), mƒô≈ºczyzna 30-40 lat, ostre rysy twarzy. K≈Ç√≥ci siƒô z wampirem.  

* *Ofiara* - mƒô≈ºczyzna 20-35 lat, piƒôkne, klasyczne rysy.  Nieprzytomna ofiara jest g≈Ç√≥wnƒÖ "dekoracjƒÖ" na du≈ºym stole w posiad≈Ço≈õci wampir√≥w. 

* *S≈Çuga* -  mƒô≈ºczyzna, 25-35 lat. Podaje kieliszki arystokratom, epicko odkrywa g≈Ç√≥wne danie na stole. Scena zawiera upadek na ziemiƒô (materac) - mile widziane osoby wysportowane lub z do≈õwiadczeniem kaskaderskim.  

* *Dziewczyna* - kobieta 20- 30 lat. Ratuje swojego ukochanego, przebierajƒÖc siƒô za s≈Çugƒô, podaje wampirom wino.

**Szczeg√≥≈Çy realizacji:**
- Jeden dzie≈Ñ zdjƒôciowy w Krakowie, wstƒôpnie planowany miƒôdzy 20-22 stycznia

- Z racji na typ projektu jeste≈õmy otwarci na wszelkich chƒôtnych, od profesjonalnych aktor√≥w po amator√≥w 

- Postacie bƒôdƒÖ charakteryzowane w peruki i  makija≈º (informacja dla os√≥b z alergiami) 
- Mimo braku bud≈ºetu produkcja ma charakter profesjonalny, cz≈Çonkowie ekipy sƒÖ osobami na co dzie≈Ñ pracujƒÖcymi w bran≈ºy filmowej, gwarantujemy du≈ºo funu i pe≈Çen profesjonalizm:)

Osoby zainteresowane udzia≈Çem proszƒô o kontakt na maila: **kingakornak@gmail.com **

wraz z przes≈Çaniem informacji o sobie: zdjƒôcia, wizyt√≥wka (najchƒôtniej w jƒôzyku angielskim, szczeg√≥lnie je≈õli to rola z tekstem), portfolio/showreel, wymiary, miasto zamieszkania.

items.text:
Now calling for a cast! I am a senior at GA State University and would like to end off my college career by bringing to life a script I wrote junior year. There will be lots of exciting things for my cast and crew such as a wrap up party the last day of filming, cast interviews posted to the Instagram production page, and first dibs on lower prices for the book to the film. I‚Äôm really hoping to start filming as soon as possible however I need more callbacks in order to start. There is no submission deadline but check out the page below for more details.

NOTE: This is not a paid role, however, it is a way to gain experience, have fun while on set, etc

I really need lots of people so like I said jsut check below and see what you know you can do/ contribute to Taylorproductions. Thanks in advance for yalls submission

attachments.ocrText: May be a graphic of text that says 'ATaylorProduction Taylo Production A TALENT/ WANT tO START YOUR ACTING JOURNEY? items.text:
Open theatre auditions coming up at The South Devon Players Theatre & Film Company, Brixham

DEVON/ OPEN BOOK PROFITSHARE / THEATRE / ANY GENDER OR ETHNICITY/

- Roles open for actors aged 16 to the sky's the limit. 

- A lot of the roles in our staging of this play  are not bound by gender; we are looking for the strongest actor for each roles. 

- Any ethnicity/ accent/ experience level equally welcome. What we are looking for are great performance skills, pleasant friendly teamwork, and the desire to be an active part of a really excellent quality show. 

- The show is set in 1793. The show is suitable for all audiences. 

- Period costumes made and supplied for all cast. 

- if you cannot make auditions on January 25th please contact us to arrange an audition over the two weeks before. 

- Actors should be based in, or have a base in, Devon because of attending rehearsals and performances. Sorry none of us who are regulars with the theatre team are in a financial or housing position to be able to put people up from further afield. We have a performance in London but have a minibus fundraised for, to get people there and back to Devon. 

- Our show teams are diverse in terms of age, experience, ethnicity and we usually have several neurodivergent team members - everyone coming on board should be willing to work as a part of a diverse group of people. 

- the show is profitshare for funding reasons. We cover rehearsal space/ costumes/ insurance etc by selling second hand bits on eBay and handmade jewellery in a couple of local shops.  This is on an open book process where ticket sales reports and any venue hire costs are shown upfront for perusal, and the ticket profits (Ticket sales less performance venue hire) are shared equally between each person in the show team. Sadly we cannot guarantee how much this is as it can vary wildly as is dependant on ticket sales. We constantly do our best to both promote the show to get those sales as high as possible and to apply for funding to bring everyone up to equity rates but this cant be guaranteed and we don‚Äôt believe in promising what we can‚Äôt guarantee to deliver. 

- ALL cast and crew also are given  access to portfolio photos and show video, copies of any press or promotional content featuring themselves, references on request (after completion of their first show run with us), and anything else that we find we can offer. 

- and - in answer to a common question we get:  nobody is ever charged anything to audition or perform with us.

Do please drop us a line with any questions not answered here or in the downloadable audition resources.

‚ú® Still time to join us at the CAL-Western NATS Conference! ‚ú®

I‚Äôm excited to share that I‚Äôll be teaching a BeSingGargle¬© workshop at the upcoming CAL-Western Region Conference of the National Association of Teachers of Singing, taking place January 16‚Äì18, 2026 (MLK Weekend) at San Jos√© State University.
https://www.calwestnats.org/reg-conference

This regional conference brings together NATS teachers and students from Arizona, California, Hawai‚Äòi, Nevada, and Utah, and I‚Äôm honored to be participating as:
üé§ A workshop presenter
üéº A judge
üåü A proud teacher with two students advancing to the semifinals

üé∂ About the BeSingGargle¬© Workshop

BeSingGargle¬© is a playful, water-based vocal warm-up designed to help singers:

 ‚Ä¢ Open range and smooth register transitions
 ‚Ä¢ Breathe with more ease and clarity
 ‚Ä¢ Shape vowels and consonants with greater freedom
 ‚Ä¢ Quickly and naturally clear phlegm while lightly lubricating the voice
 ‚Ä¢ Calm nerves and boost confidence through gentle vagal and sensory activation

A special bonus: BeSingGargle¬© works beautifully online, making it a powerful and engaging tool for virtual voice lessons as well as in-person teaching.

The session will include a live demonstration, a student demo, and hands-on participation. It‚Äôs joyful, grounding, and surprisingly effective, helping singers move out of their heads, into their bodies, and onto the stage with confidence and ease. 

‚è∞ Late registration is still open!

If you‚Äôd like to attend the conference and join this workshop, you can sign up here:

üëâ Late Registration Form:

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd6zm-XCK_3FYN4qZSLzsTSoV7pH5zXuL-yXW9LvW5NU_aJwA/viewform

I‚Äôd love to see fellow teachers, singers, and students there for a weekend of learning, connection, and inspired singing. üé∂‚ú®

2025 NATS Cal-Western Region Conference Registration

sharedPost.text:
Let's talk momentum not "some day"

Every role, every breakthrough, every turning point begins long before the camera rolls.

At Casting Calls UK, we believe real careers aren‚Äôt built on vague dreams or distant timelines. They‚Äôre built in six month windows.

Six months is long enough to grow.
Long enough to learn, stretch, and sharpen your craft.
But short enough to stay hungry, focused, and accountable.

This industry doesn‚Äôt reward waiting.
It rewards action, clarity, and consistency.

So pause for a moment.
Grab a notebook. Your notes app. Or use the comments right here.

üëá Tell us:

What do you want to achieve in the next six months?
Where do you want to be in your career by then?

Write it down.
See it clearly.
Commit to it fully.

Because when you give your ambition a deadline, it stops being a wish and starts becoming a plan.

‚ÄúTalent opens the door. Commitment decides how far you walk through it.‚Äù

‚Äî Casting Calls UK

Clarity sharpens focus.
Focus shapes behaviour.
And behaviour is what changes careers.

Your next six months start now.

Just a heads up, some paid and urgent casting roles do land on our main page first, 

We sometimes share paid, time sensitive casting opportunities on our main page first alongside industry news..

Following it just means you‚Äôre less likely to miss something useful when it drops.
üëâ https://www.facebook.com/castingcallsuk üé¨üá¨üáß

items.text:
FEBRUARY CLASS IS NOW ON SALE

WHAT: SCRIPTED STAGEFIGHTING
A practical, high-energy workshop focused on safe, believable stagefighting and grounded dramatic performance.

This session will introduce the fundamentals of scripted stagefighting ‚Äî including safety, intention, physical storytelling, and camera awareness ‚Äî before building those skills into a filmed dramatic scene.

Actors will:
 ‚Ä¢ Learn the basics of stagefighting technique and safety
 ‚Ä¢ Explore how conflict, stakes, and character drive physical action
 ‚Ä¢ Work with scripted material to choreograph and rehearse a fight sequence
 ‚Ä¢ Film the scene, focusing on truth, tension, and clarity on camera

The emphasis is on storytelling through conflict, not flashy moves ‚Äî making the work honest, controlled, and usable for screen or stage.

WHEN:
Saturday 7th February 2026
2‚Äì5pm

WHERE:
The Crescent Theatre, Birmingham

If you‚Äôd like to book then email estherstanford@icloud.com, DM or go through www.estherstanford.co.uk

#stagefighting #theworkshopactorsstudio #birmingham #actingclass

We‚Äôre still looking to cast the following roles for our original cabaret musical **A Place Not Mine**, set in the world of **Novattera University**.

**RIVEN** ‚Äì emotionally complex, introspective, with strong inner conflict

**AURORA** ‚Äì warm, playful, brings light and humour into heavy moments
**SELENE** ‚Äì sharp, witty, loyal, not afraid to speak her mind
**ORIS** ‚Äì kind, quirky, emotionally open, using humour to cope

**ELARA** ‚Äì intelligent, anxious, loyal, quietly funny

‚Ä¢ Two singing videos (one musical theatre song + one song of your choice)

items.text:
üé¨ ACTORS: Stop waiting for a Casting Director to "discover" you. Let‚Äôs build the reel that gets you hired.

I run **Kollective Kandor**, a creative ecosystem in LA. We are gearing up for a heavy slate of **Commercials, Branded Docs, and Narrative Shorts** in Q1, and I am opening up our **Internal Casting Roster.**

**Here is how we operate differently:** Most productions treat actors like props. We treat you like **Partners.**

**‚úÖ THE OFFER:**
* **Agency Over Typecasting:** We prioritize actors who want to break the mold. Need a dramatic scene to balance your comedy reel? You can *request* that role, and we align scripts to fit.
* **High-End Production:** We provide the full crew, cinema cameras, and post-production for free. You walk away with broadcast-quality footage, not grainy iPhone clips.
* **Community:** You join a network of filmmakers who hire from within.

**‚õî THE CATCH (Read this):** We operate on a **Mutual Investment Model.** There is no day rate. Everyone on set (DP, Director, Producer) is investing their time to create high-level assets for everyone‚Äôs portfolio.
* **If you are strictly looking for paid gigs right now:** I respect that, but please keep scrolling.
* **If you are looking for specific experience and top-tier footage:** We are your team.

**HOW TO JOIN:** We don't spam. You will be added to our **Casting Blast** to get notified of roles before they go public.

**Drop your info here to get on the Roster:** üëâ [https://tally.so/r/nGVyoe](https://tally.so/r/nGVyoe)

Let‚Äôs build. üèÅ

#Acting #LosAngeles #Casting #ActorsLife #ReelBuilder #KollectiveKandor

**üé• Currently Casting: FREE DECLUTTERING & ORGANIZING HELP (LOS ANGELES)**

Currently looking for people in the Los Angeles area for upcoming episodes of The Carla Project, a popular YouTube channel focused on decluttering and organizing.

Selected participants receive free, hands-on decluttering and organizing help in exchange for being filmed. The process focuses on decluttering one room at a time, and participants must be comfortable sharing the experience on camera.

Specifically looking for:

‚Ä¢ Chronically messy or disorganized homes
‚Ä¢ Very cluttered spaces that feel overwhelming
‚Ä¢ Small spaces such as studios, tiny homes, bachelor pads, and apartments
‚Ä¢ People at a turning point including downsizing, inherited homes, post-divorce resets, or aspiring minimalists fed up with how they‚Äôve been living

Common spaces include kitchens, closets, bedrooms, offices, living rooms, pantries, and wardrobes.

To apply, please email thecarlaprojectcasting@gmail.com with:

‚Ä¢ A brief description of the space and photos
‚Ä¢ Why you‚Äôre ready to declutter now (bonus if submitted as a 30 second video)
‚Ä¢ Where you‚Äôre located and who you share your home with

Please watch an episode of The Carla Project before submitting to get a sense of the channel. Episode linked in comments.

**++++Doku: Protagonisten gesucht++++**

*Kein Schauspiel-Job, aber vielleicht gibt's ja unter euch Menschen, die noch einen ganz anderen Traum haben...? *

**Bundesweit / Protagonisten (m/f/d), 30 - 50 Jahre f√ºr Doku-Serie, bei der wir Deinen Traum im europ√§ischen Ausland testen / 8 - 14 Drehtage im Mai 2026 / wir zahlen alle Reisekosten, Aufenthalt vor Ort**
 
Du hast einen Traum von einem ganz bestimmten Beruf in einem anderen Land in Europa? Vielleicht wolltest du immer eine Eisdiele in Italien leiten, in Schweden in einem Design-Studio arbeiten oder eine  Strandbar auf Mallorca √ºbernehmen ‚Äì nicht als Urlaub, sondern als echter Arbeitsalltag.

Doch dann kam das Leben dazwischen: Ausbildung oder Studium, ein fester Job. Verantwortung. Sicherheit. Und irgendwann vielleicht auch Familie, Kinder, Verpflichtungen. Pl√∂tzlich ging es nicht mehr nur um dich allein ‚Äì und der Traum r√ºckte immer weiter in den Hintergrund. Aber ganz verschwunden ist er nie. Und der Gedanke daran l√§sst dich immer noch nicht los. Dann melde dich bei uns!

Wir von der Produktionsfirma Picture Punks wollen diesen Traum gemeinsam mit dir testen ‚Äì realistisch, ehrlich und ohne Drehbuch. F√ºr eine Doku-Serie begleiten wir dich dabei, deinen lange gehegten Traum im europ√§ischen Ausland wirklich auszuprobieren. Die Dreharbeiten im Mai 2026 dauern etwa ein bis zwei Wochen. Wir √ºbernehmen alle Reisekosten und k√ºmmern uns um den Aufenthalt vor Ort.

Wichtig ist uns: Du hast einen echten, lange gehegten Traum, keinen spontanen Wunsch. Du willst wissen, ob dieses Leben ‚Äì auch mit Familie, Verantwortung oder Kindern ‚Äì wirklich funktionieren k√∂nnte. Du bist bereit, dich offen auf dieses Experiment einzulassen und du m√∂chtest Teil einer authentischen Doku-Serie sein.

Wir starten mit einem Interview in Deutschland bei Dir zu Hause und begleiten Dich dann √ºber etwa ein bis zwei Wochen ins Ausland, w√§hrend Du Deinen Traum testest. Und wir treffen dich sp√§ter zu Hause noch mal wieder, wenn du am Ende ein Fazit ziehst: War es so sch√∂n, wie Du es Dir immer vorgestellt hast? W√§re das ein Leben f√ºr immer? items.text:
Open theatre auditions coming up at The South Devon Players Theatre & Film Company, Brixham

DEVON/ OPEN BOOK PROFITSHARE / THEATRE / ANY GENDER OR ETHNICITY/

- Roles open for actors aged 16 to the sky's the limit. 

- A lot of the roles in our staging of this play  are not bound by gender; we are looking for the strongest actor for each roles. 

- Any ethnicity/ accent/ experience level equally welcome. What we are looking for are great performance skills, pleasant friendly teamwork, and the desire to be an active part of a really excellent quality show. 

- The show is set in 1793. The show is suitable for all audiences. 

- Period costumes made and supplied for all cast. 

- if you cannot make auditions on January 25th please contact us to arrange an audition over the two weeks before. 

- Actors should be based in, or have a base in, Devon because of attending rehearsals and performances. Sorry none of us who are regulars with the theatre team are in a financial or housing position to be able to put people up from further afield. We have a performance in London but have a minibus fundraised for, to get people there and back to Devon. 

- Our show teams are diverse in terms of age, experience, ethnicity and we usually have several neurodivergent team members - everyone coming on board should be willing to work as a part of a diverse group of people. 

- the show is profitshare for funding reasons. We cover rehearsal space/ costumes/ insurance etc by selling second hand bits on eBay and handmade jewellery in a couple of local shops.  This is on an open book process where ticket sales reports and any venue hire costs are shown upfront for perusal, and the ticket profits (Ticket sales less performance venue hire) are shared equally between each person in the show team. Sadly we cannot guarantee how much this is as it can vary wildly as is dependant on ticket sales. We constantly do our best to both promote the show to get those sales as high as possible and to apply for funding to bring everyone up to equity rates but this cant be guaranteed and we don‚Äôt believe in promising what we can‚Äôt guarantee to deliver. 

- ALL cast and crew also are given  access to portfolio photos and show video, copies of any press or promotional content featuring themselves, references on request (after completion of their first show run with us), and anything else that we find we can offer. 

- and - in answer to a common question we get:  nobody is ever charged anything to audition or perform with us.

Do please drop us a line with any questions not answered here or in the downloadable audition resources.

items.text:
Actors/Actresses Wanted For Storytelling Fine Art Fantasy Shoots. TFP ONLY. Shoots based around the UK.
I am a fantasy and fairytale photographer with 15 years experience in both natural light photography and digital art, painting and photoshop. I am a hobbyist who enjoys location shoots for the right aesthetic to every shot. I do this for the love of creating, not for money or fame. This isnt my job and I believe thats why my entire heart and soul goes into every image I create. 

I am looking for actors and actresses who are serious about telling their own stories through their art, who can or are willing to learn to emote, who have drive and passion for creating unique images that bring to life characters and themes. There's no requirements on height, look, ethnicity or size. Please note that if you apply to this project I will select the best individuals for this project and test shoot with them first. 

Models must be happy to travel as I have various locations to use at my disposal already.  Travel would be reimbursed after the shoot takes place. If you have location's near you I am happy to travel but only for the right places. 

I will loan and lend outfits I own or props for these shoots. There's potentially also a designer on board for the females for my shoots for 2026. I am currently in search for someone who can loan male costumes. 

Styling of makeup and hair is down to the models themselves unless stated otherwise. 

You will be provided with the following for every shoot. Up to 10 images per shoot, 1 digital artwork, BTS videos and a fashion video. 

If this is of interest to you as a model/actor or actress please connect with me via messaging me directly on here or through Instagram.

 www.instagram.com/lensoflegends

CASTING CALL ‚Äì Unpaid short proof-of-concept scenes (London)
Hi everyone, 

I‚Äôm shooting a few key scenes (10-15 minutes total) from a prestige drama pilot I‚Äôve written ‚Äì slow-burn character piece, strong roles. 

**Unpaid** (no/low budget) but you get:

- Professionally edited showreel footage (I edit in DaVinci Resolve)

- IMDb credit

- Meals + travel expenses covered in London

- Copy of the finished piece 

**Shoot**: 2‚Äì3 flexible days in Feb/March 2026  

**Locations**: Simple ‚Äì office (evening), restaurant, riverside path (all London, easy access) 

**Roles**:

- Female lead, 23-28, quietly pretty, thoughtful/subtle emotion

- Female supporting, 25-30, funny, chaotic energy, warm best friend

- Male supporting, 23-28, ginger/red hair, heavier build, gentle/kind (mostly visual)

- Male 45-60, working-class dad, short scene

- Female 45-60, warm mum (voice only) 

No experience required if you fit the look and can bring real emotion. 

Send a quick self-tape or photo + short intro to my DM. 

Thanks!

Viele von ihnen wurden in Schauspiel- und People-Agenturen aufgenommen, bekamen Rollen, Engagements oder Preise. Nicht weil sie ‚Äûfertig‚Äú waren, sondern weil sie wirkten.

 

Im Oktober waren wir vier Tage lang in Irland. Showrealszenen, Embodiment, Natur, Workshops, Luxus, Stille, Tiefgang. Dort ist klar geworden: Technik reicht nicht. Pr√§senz entscheidet.

 

Damit entstand die Essenz-Methode.

 

Eine Methode aus Schauspiel, Nervensystem, Kamera, Energie und Embodiment ‚Äì in 7 Buchstaben:

E ‚Äì Erleben

S ‚Äì Selbst

S ‚Äì Seele

E ‚Äì Emotion

N ‚Äì N√§he

Z ‚Äì Zwischen den Zeilen

 

2026 werden wir diese Methode weitergeben.

Erster Schritt: **Essenz-Workshop am 10. Januar.**

# Method Acting Grundkurs
Beginn Mittwoch, 14. Januar 2026
[Sichere dir jetzt einen Kursplatz!](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)
**Du willst:**

¬∑ die Schauspielmethode lernen, die sich in den letzten 100 Jahren weltweit durchgesetzt hat

¬∑ echt, authentisch, glaubw√ºrdig, wahrhaftig, ber√ºhrend und bewegend spielen

¬∑ deinen einzigartigen Weg zur Figur finden

¬∑ dich in Gef√ºhle und Zust√§nde einer Rolle hineinversetzen k√∂nnen

¬∑ deine Atmung und Stimme entwickeln

¬∑ deine K√∂rpersprache in einer motivierten Gruppe von Gleichgesinnten entwickeln

¬∑ organisch die Objektarbeit in dein Schauspiel integrieren

¬∑ lernen, wie man effektiv und effizient Texte auswendig lernt

¬∑ deine mentale St√§rke aufbauen

¬∑ die bew√§hrten Kursunterlagen erhalten und dich von ausgesuchten Videobeispielen inspirieren lassen

¬∑ 24 Stunden praktische Erfahrung sammeln

¬∑ ein Teilnahmezertifikat erhalten

¬∑ von mehr als 40 Jahren Berufserfahrung profitieren

[Dann ist dieser Kurs genau das richtige f√ºr DICH!](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

Und das sagen Teilnehmer*innen:

‚ÄûAuf jeden Fall wird meine Reise bei Dir weiter gehen. Ich bin begeistert, wie Du f√∂rderst und forderst und uns dabei hilfst, den n√§chsten Schritt zu wagen und zu gehen.‚Äú I.

‚ÄûHallo Marco, ich profitiere noch immer von deinem Kurs im Playbacktheater *, in dem ich seit etwa 10 Jahren dabei bin.‚Äú H.

‚ÄûHerzlichen Dank an dich f√ºr den belebenden und lehrreichen Kurs, sowie deine Offenheit.‚Äú E.

‚ÄûMir macht der Method Acting Kurs grosse Freude, die individuelle Arbeit gef√§llt mir sehr.‚Äú S.

‚Äûheute erlebt und umgesetzt. ‚Ä¶ einfach spannend bei dir im unterricht. jedes wort stimmt. danke marco.‚Äú R.

‚ÄûDanke f√ºr den interessanten Kurs. Ich lerne viel und bin auch froh, um die gute Dokumentation, die uns zu Verf√ºgung steht.‚Äú D.

‚Äû√úbrigens, ich habe die Stunde letztes Mal super gefunden ‚Äì ich kam todm√ºde an und ging wacher und selbstbewusster nach Hause. Danke daf√ºr!‚Äú A.

‚ÄûErst mal Danke das Du mich aus der Komfortzone herausgeholt hast, dein Kurs war sehr hilfreich.‚Äú P.

‚ÄûYour training helped, Marco. A teammate told me it was ‚Äûlike real method acting‚Äú. I told them I took method acting. They didn‚Äôt know that when hiring me.‚Äú A.

(Die Testimonials sind aus Datenschutzgr√ºnden anonymisiert. Du willst noch mehr Testimonials? Dann lese auf der [Website](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/) und auf Google weiter.)

Du willst es genau wissen. Auf der Website findest du alles, was du brauchst:

‚Ä¢ Alle [Details](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/) zum Kurs

‚Ä¢ [Testimonials / Bewertungen](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

‚Ä¢ Die [Anmeldung](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

[Was h√§lt dich auf?](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

Kursleitung: Marco Hausammann-Gilardi hat mehr als 40 Jahre Erfahrung als Schauspieler, Autor, Regisseur und Produzent in Theater, Film und Fernsehen. Er war von 1986 bis 1988 an Strasberg‚Äôs Real Stage, bei Ernie Martin (Artistic Director Actor‚Äôs Studio Los Angeles) und am Actor‚Äôs Studio New York (PO). Seit 1988 unterrichtet er auf dieser Basis und seinen praktischen Berufserfahrungen. Er ist Mitglied folgender Berufsverb√§nde:

‚Ä¢ t. Theaterschaffende der Schweiz/Professionnels du spectacle Suisse/Professionisti dello spettacolo Svizzera

‚Ä¢ Verband Filmregie und Drehbuch Schweiz ARF/FDS

‚Ä¢ Verband f√ºr Film- und Fernsehdramaturgie e.V. VeDRA

[ZES Zentrum f√ºr Entwicklung im Schauspiel](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

Das Kompetenzzentrum f√ºr Method Acting
